main event: A 13-year-old boy named Robert J. Salvo reported seeing a saucer-shaped object over Wall Township, New Jersey on March 30, 1966.
interesting points: Salvo said the object made a 'loud whirring sound' and shot out of a cloud, hovered over him, and then quickly disappeared.
Salvo took several photographs of the object, which were later obtained by the Army and sent to the Air Force for investigation.
The photographs were described as showing a circular object with a domed upper surface and a cylindrical protrusion.
Authorities were unable to determine the exact nature or identity of the object due to a lack of key information such as camera focal length and distance to the object.
Despite the lack of definitive analysis, the incident received significant media attention and public interest in the local area.
